#   CODE-003: dog: collapse table-scan & twin helper dups

dog repeats several small structural blocks: dog_proj_lookup/DOGIsTransport/DOGIsGitTransport walk a string table with the same loop, the ron60→time_t conversion is pasted across HUNK.c, WHIFF's 40/60 hashlet helpers are byte-twins on one shift constant, and ULOGVerbColor/ULOGVerbTag scan one table identically. Factor each into a single parameterized helper.

##  Issues

Repeated string-table scans, a 4x ron60→time_t block, and width-twinned helpers.

 -  dog_proj_lookup/DOGIsTransport/DOGIsGitTransport (DOG.c:61,87,104) = same NUL-table walk + u8csEq.
 -  ron60→time_t now/mktime block pasted in HUNK.c:52,85,392.
 -  WHIFFHashlet40/60, HexFeed40/60, HexHashlet40/60 (WHIFF.h:111-135) differ only by a 24-vs-4 shift.
 -  ULOGVerbColor/ULOGVerbTag (ULOG.c:1219,1228) scan ULOG_VERB_TAGS identically, differing only in the return.

##  Blockers

None; dog-internal. Shares DOG.c/HUNK.c with CODE-002, so land in the same dog worktree, serially.

##  Planned

One helper per duplicated shape; parameterize the differing value.

 -  Repro first (§17): keep existing dog tests green; add a case per collapsed helper if uncovered.
 -  String-table walk → one DOGTableLookup(table,key).
 -  ron60→time_t → one HUNK helper; WHIFF 40/60 → one width-param helper.
 -  ULOG verb table → one lookup returning the row; color/tag derive from it.

